For a moment, there is nothing but the shock of existence. No memories tame me; no future comforts me. I am the rupture and the repair in one, the wild birth and the trembling aftermath.
My past is the emptiness I shattered to be here. My future is unformed, still curled in the dark. All that exists is this raw, unsteady now.
In this brutal now, I am alive.
